{
  "stem": "21308.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- but we-- we knew that, you know, things were pretty bad.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we didn't know they were as bad as they were.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Could we trust the news?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I certainly trusted it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The British news, the BBC.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The BBC, I believe, was the only news which was trustworthy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The nine o'clock news used to be preceded by the three dots and a dash, the V-sign, da-da-da-da, da-da-da-da, da-da-da-da.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And people all over Europe risked their lives to listen to it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That news was good because it was only a fragment mews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Are you with me?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was just a fragment of news, but it was-- it was truthful.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we finished with-- when we finished the campaign on the [INAUDIBLE], we came to a small village called Vught in Holland-- V-U-G-H-T, Vught.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then when we learned that there had been in Vught a concentration camp-- now, that was the first concentration camp which we ever heard about.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't go into it, we didn't go near it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we heard there had been a concentration camp there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We knew that there had been evacuation of Jews because various people told us, oh, that house was owned by Jews that they've been taken away.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we didn't know of it as a program.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think the-- when we were going into Germany and we got halfway across Germany and we had a very big battle on the River Aller, we-- we had a-- it was a good old scrum.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But anyway, we won and we were actually-- although we didn't know it, we were actually heading towards Belsen concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, that was the first time we really heard of these camps.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
